{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}} The '''serpentine system''' is a method employed in the organization of a [[competition]] to define the [[Single-elimination tournament#Seeding|seeded]] teams and arrange them in pools. The ''n'' ranked teams that will be involved in the [[tournament]] are distributed in ''m'' pools according to the following [[algorithm]]:
{| border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="{ font-size:smaller; }" |- bgcolor="#efefef" !Pool 1!!Pool 2!! . . . !!Pool ''m'' − 1!!Pool ''m'' |- align="center" |1||2|| . . . ||''m'' − 1||''m'' |- align="center" |2''m''||2''m'' − 1|| . . . ||''m'' + 2||''m'' + 1 |- align="center" |2''m'' + 1||2''m'' + 2|| . . . ||3''m'' − 1||3''m'' |- align="center" |...||&nbsp;||&nbsp;||&nbsp;||&nbsp; |}
For instance, 12 teams would be organized in four-team pools, according to the serpentine system, as follows:
{| border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="font-size:smaller" |- bgcolor="#efefef" !Pool 1!!Pool 2!!Pool 3 |- align="center" |1||2||3 |- align="center" |6||5||4 |- align="center" |7||8||9 |- align="center" |12||11||10 |}
To improve competitivity, this method is sometimes used in conjunction with the [[Drawing straws|drawing of lots]] method: the serpentine system is used only for some of the teams involved in a competition ("seeds"); the rest is distributed in pools following a drawing of lots.
